Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest chapter set-title

chapter set-title

Purpose:
  Rename an existing chapter in the archive TOC.

Usage:
  spinedigest chapter set-title <path> --chapter <id> --title <title> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Behavior:
  - Updates only the chapter title stored in the TOC.
  - Does not change source text, graph nodes, summaries, or metadata.
  - Pass an empty or whitespace-only `--title` value to clear the title and show `[untitled]`.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.

Output shape:
  Prints the updated chapter status.

Examples:
  spinedigest chapter set-title book.sdpub --chapter 12 --title "New Chapter Title"
  spinedigest chapter set-title book.sdpub --chapter 12 --title ""

See also:
  - spinedigest chapter list --help
  - spinedigest chapter status --help
  - spinedigest help command
